From f6dbe9e5e31e0177e79d30492f46a558c062b589 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 09:36:01 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add per-sink volume control for custom sinks

- Adds `Volume` field (0-100) to `CustomSinkConfiguration` for YAML persistence
- Persisted volume is automatically re-applied after a sink is loaded or reloaded
- New `PUT /api/sinks/{name}/volume` endpoint sets PulseAudio sink volume and saves it
- `CustomSinksService` gains `SetSinkVolumeAsync` / `GetSinkVolumeAsync` backed by `VolumeCommandRunner`
- Sink cards in the UI now show a volume slider when the sink is in Loaded state; changes are debounced and sent to the API

https://claude.ai/code/session_014XhFbgSHBru2ZFTLFXKdTG
